**CFI PROMPT SERIES --- S1 DYNAMIC MACHINERY CALCULATOR**

**CALCULATOR HUB ARCHITECTURE**

Auto-Scaling · Equipment Sizing · Building Design · CAPEX · OPEX · ASCII
Flow · Architecture

v2.0 \| March 2026 \| Design Basis: 60 TPH FFB Mill, Bogor, West Java

> **CORE PRINCIPLE: When S0 throughput (t/h) changes for ANY residue
> stream, the S1 Calculator IMMEDIATELY re-runs all eight downstream
> calculators, redesigns the equipment register, resizes the building,
> recalculates CAPEX/OPEX, regenerates the ASCII flow, and relays the
> updated S2 handoff to Supabase --- with ZERO manual re-entry.**
>
> **BACKUP UNIT RULE (IMMUTABLE): Every machine with motor \>11 kW OR
> classified as a press, shredder, mill, trommel, or decanter MUST have
> a minimum 1 hot standby backup unit of identical specification. We
> never operate at full nameplate capacity. Target utilisation ≤80% of
> derated capacity at all times.**

**0. S1 CALCULATOR HUB --- FULL CONNECTION MAP**

The S1 Calculator is the master engineering engine for the S1
pre-processing facility. It receives throughput data from S0, applies
automatic scaling logic, and simultaneously drives eight subordinate
calculators covering equipment, footprint, building structure, CAPEX,
OPEX, process flow visualisation, architectural design, and NPK relay.

