**CALC-A** **EQUIPMENT SELECTION & SIZING CALCULATOR**

*First calculator in the chain --- determines duty and backup units for
every machine across all three processing lines*

**Purpose**

Receives stream t/h from S0 via the S1 core, queries the Supabase
equipment_catalogue, applies the scaling decision tree (Section 1.2) for
every equipment type in the EFB, OPDC, and POS processing lines, and
outputs the complete versioned equipment register for this run.

**CALC-A Inputs**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Input**        **Source**              **Guardrail**
  ---------------- ----------------------- ------------------------------
  EFB t/h (fresh   S0 output               Design basis: 25 t/h
  weight)                                  

  OPDC t/h (fresh  S0 output               LOCKED: 15.2% of EFB fresh
  weight)                                  weight --- never change

  POS t/h (fresh   S0 output               Default: \~1.25 t/h; ICP Fe
  weight)                                  result may reduce inclusion

  Equipment        Supabase                65%/85% derate must be applied
  catalogue        equipment_catalogue     before sizing

  User-preferred   Admin Panel or system   Professor #22 validates any
  OEM              default (✅ =           non-default selection
                   recommended)            

  Utilisation      System default: ≤80% \| Hard ceiling: 85% utilisation
  target %         User may tighten to 70% = RED, must resolve
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**CALC-A Outputs → All downstream calculators**

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Output Field**     **Description**                **Recipient**
  -------------------- ------------------------------ ----------------------
  equipment_register   Full list: tag, name,          CALC-B, C, D, E, F, G,
  JSON                 duty_units, backup_units,      H
                       total_units, util_pct,         
                       motor_kw, footprint L/W/H,     
                       oem, model, unit_cost,         
                       total_cost, lead_time          

  Utilisation          RED / AMBER / GREEN per        Display UI + CALC-D
  traffic-light table  machine per stream             notes

  Total connected load Sum of all motors × duty units CALC-C electrical
  kW                   across entire facility         sizing

  Equipment footprint  L × W per machine × unit count CALC-B floor plan
  list                 (separate per line)            

  CAPEX subtotal ---   Unit cost × total units, by    CALC-D
  equipment supply     line and aggregate             
  only                                                

  Scaling change flags Machines where unit count      Alert display,
                       changed vs. prior run          change_log Supabase
                                                      write

  DATA GAP list        Any machine where cost source  CALC-D flagging, CFO
                       = estimate not quote           review gate
  --------------------------------------------------------------------------

> **CALC-A GUARDRAIL: No machine may pass to S2 with util_pct \> 85% of
> derated capacity. CALC-A must resolve by adding a duty unit or
> recommending a larger model before the run proceeds.**
>
> **OPDC YIELD LOCK: OPDC t/h is always calculated as 15.2% of EFB fresh
> weight. CALC-A must never accept an independently entered OPDC rate
> that contradicts this.**

**CALC-B** **FOOTPRINT & FLOOR PLAN CALCULATOR**

*Translates equipment register into minimum building floor area with
full maintenance clearances, lane widths, and platform schedules*

**Purpose**

Takes the equipment register from CALC-A and computes the minimum
building floor area. It arranges equipment in process sequence, applies
mandatory clearance and aisle rules, sizes platforms, positions MCC
rooms and maintenance workshop, and outputs the complete building
envelope dimensions.

**Floor Plan Rules (All Mandatory)**

  -------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Rule**           **Value**      **Rationale**
  ------------------ -------------- ---------------------------------------
  Side clearance     Min 1.0 m each Operator access, guarding, inspection
  each machine       side           

  Drive / discharge  Min 1.5 m      Motor replacement, shaft extraction
  end clearance                     

  Central            6.0 m (full    Forklift passage + maintenance crew +
  maintenance aisle  building       2-person clearance
  width              length)        

  Elevated platform  Min 2.5 m      2 operators + hand tools side-by-side
  width                             

  Staircase          1.5 m × 3.0 m  Building codes + emergency egress
  footprint          (one per 2     
                     platforms)     

  MCC rooms          Two rooms, 6 × Electrical separation, heat ventilation
                     4 m each, at   
                     building NE    
                     and NW corners 

  Maintenance        10 × 10 m      Welding, lathe, tool storage, spare
  workshop bay       attached to    parts
                     north end of   
                     building       

  Truck receiving    18 × 12 m (EFB Truck turning radius 9 m, separate fire
  bay                and OPDC       zone
                     shared),       
                     physically     
                     separate from  
                     processing     
                     hall           

  POS sump and       6 × 4 m        Spill containment, chemical resistance
  decanter pad       reinforced     
                     slab at ground 
                     level,         
                     adjacent to    
                     south wall     

  Buffer silos       Ø3.0 m EFB     Product surge buffering before S2
  (EFB + OPDC)       silo + Ø2.8 m  gallery
                     OPDC silo, end 
                     of respective  
                     lines          

  Covered conveyor   4 m wide ×     Weather protection of product stream
  gallery to S2      measured       
                     distance       
                     (calculated    
                     per site plan) 

  Emergency exit     Min 3 m        NFPA 101 / Indonesian fire code
  clearance          unobstructed   
                     path to all    
                     exit doors     
  -------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Floor Plan Calculation Logic**

> CALC-B FLOOR PLAN ALGORITHM:
>
> ── INPUT: equipment_register from CALC-A
> ───────────────────────────────
>
> For each machine: footprint_L_m, footprint_W_m, unit_count,
> process_sequence
>
> Clearance rules (above), fixed rooms (MCC, workshop, silos, bay)
>
> ── STEP 1: EFB LINE WIDTH
> ───────────────────────────────────────────────
>
> efb_max_equip_width = MAX(footprint_W) across all EFB machines
>
> efb_line_width = efb_max_equip_width + 2 × 1.0 (side clearances)
>
> Round up to next 3 m module
>
> ── STEP 2: OPDC LINE WIDTH (mirrors EFB)
> ───────────────────────────────
>
> opdc_line_width = MAX(footprint_W OPDC) + 2 × 1.0
>
> Round up to next 3 m module
>
> ── STEP 3: TOTAL BUILDING WIDTH
> ────────────────────────────────────────
>
> total_width = efb_line_width + 6.0 (central aisle) + opdc_line_width
>
> Round up to next 6 m portal frame bay width
>
> ── STEP 4: BUILDING DEPTH
> ───────────────────────────────────────────────
>
> For EFB line: SUM(footprint_L per machine + 1.5 m end clearance) in
>
> process sequence order
>
> For OPDC line: same calculation
>
> depth_basis = MAX(efb_depth, opdc_depth) + workshop zone (10 m) + silo
> zone (4 m)
>
> Round up to next 5 m portal frame module
>
> ── STEP 5: REQUIRED CLEAR HEIGHT
> ───────────────────────────────────────
>
> platform_max_elevation = MAX across all platform heights (from
> equipment dimensions)
>
> required_clear_ht = platform_max_elevation + 2.5 m (headroom above
> platform)
>
> Frame clear height → round up to: 8 / 10 / 12 / 14 m
>
> ── STEP 6: OUTPUT
> ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
>
> { building_width_m, building_depth_m, clear_height_m, floor_area_m2,
>
> portal_frame_count, bay_spacing_m, platform_schedule\[\],
>
> equipment_grid_positions{tag: {x_m, y_m, elevation_m}} }

