**C.2 Conveyor Network Design Logic**

All conveyors are designed by CALC-C using equipment positions from
CALC-B. Each conveyor is sized for the stream t/h it carries.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Conveyor         **Calculation Rule**
  Parameter**        
  ------------------ ----------------------------------------------------
  Belt width (mm)    EFB line: max(600, CEIL(stream_tph / 35) × 100).
                     OPDC line: max(500, CEIL(stream_tph / 25) × 100).
                     Gallery: same as line width at discharge.

  Belt speed (m/s)   1.0--1.5 m/s on feeders and horizontal runs.
                     0.75--1.0 m/s on inclines \>15°. All VFD-controlled.

  Incline angle      ≤18° without cleats. ≤22° with 50 mm rubber cleats
                     at 300 mm pitch. If elevation change \>3 m over \<10
                     m horizontal → cleated belt mandatory.

  Drive motor kW     P_motor = (stream_tph × 9.81 × (L × friction_0.022 +
                     H)) / (3600 × efficiency_0.85). Add 15% safety
                     factor. Select next standard motor
                     (7.5/11/15/18.5/22/30 kW).

  Idler type and     Troughing 35° triple-roll idlers @ 1.2 m loaded, 3.0
  spacing            m return. Impact idlers at feed points (5-roll,
                     rubber disc).

  Transfer chutes    Lined with 12 mm UHMW-PE or 20 mm polyurethane.
                     Minimum 600 mm clearance above belt. Dust seal
                     flaps. Dead-box impact zone.

  Belt material      4-ply EP rubber, 10 mm top cover, 4 mm bottom.
                     Suitable for wet fibrous palm residues. OR PVC
                     food-grade on product streams post-S3.

  Belt alignment     Auto-tracking training idlers at feed and discharge
                     on all belts \>10 m. Belt-track switches trip on
                     deviation \>50 mm.

  Safety systems     Pull-cord (rip-cord) switches full length both
                     sides. Zero-speed sensor on tail pulley. Belt-sway
                     switches × 2 per conveyor. Guarding per ISO 11684.

  Total conveyor     EFB line: 9 conveyors. OPDC line: 5 conveyors. POS
  count --- base     line: 2 conveyors. Covered gallery to S2: 3
  case 25 t/h EFB    conveyors. TOTAL: 19 conveyors.

  Motor total ---    Sum of all drive motor ratings (kW) → feeds into
  all conveyors      CALC-C electrical connected load total.
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**C.3 Electrical Design Logic**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Item**           **Calculation**
  ------------------ ----------------------------------------------------
  Total connected    Sum of CALC-A equipment motors + CALC-C conveyor
  load (kW)          motors + 15% allowance for lighting, HVAC,
                     instrumentation, small power.

  Demand factor      0.75 applied to all processing equipment (not all
                     running simultaneously). 1.0 for lighting, controls,
                     emergency systems.

  Transformer kVA    kVA = (total demand kW × demand_factor) /
                     power_factor_0.92. Then × 1.25 safety margin. Select
                     next standard: 250 / 315 / 400 / 500 / 630 / 800
                     kVA.

  PLN grid           LV 380V 3-phase 50 Hz. Metering panel at perimeter
  connection         wall. PLN tariff \$0.091437/kWh (IDR/USD 15,800).
                     Flag for AI search update every 3 days.

  LV switchboard     Main incomer MCCB. Bus-bar sized for full connected
                     load. Separate circuits for EFB line, OPDC line,
                     POS, lighting, services.

  MCC panels         One MCC per processing line (EFB and OPDC). DOL
                     starters ≤7.5 kW. Star-delta starters 11--37 kW. VFD
                     for all feeders, conveyors, and variable-speed
                     machines.

  PLC and HMI        Allen-Bradley or Siemens S7 PLC (one per MCC).
                     15-inch touchscreen HMI per line. Remote monitoring
                     via Supabase API integration (OPC-UA or MQTT
                     bridge).

  Instrumentation    Belt scales on all product conveyors (output feed to
                     NPK Relay). Level sensors on all silos and hoppers.
                     Moisture sensors post-press discharge (alarms if
                     OPDC \>40% MC).

  Earthing system    TN-C-S. Earth grid 25 × 4 mm copper tape buried 600
                     mm depth around building perimeter. All equipment
                     bonded. Earth loop impedance ≤1 Ω.
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**CALC-D** **MACHINERY CAPEX CALCULATOR**

*Calculates full capital expenditure for all S1 machinery and
civil/structural works --- dynamically updates on every scaling run*

**Purpose**

Aggregates equipment supply costs from CALC-A, structural and conveyor
costs from CALC-C, and building civil costs from CALC-B into a single
versioned CAPEX statement. Every line item is traceable to a source (OEM
quote / contractor estimate / engineering estimate / DATA GAP).

**CAPEX Calculation Logic**

> FOR each machine_item IN equipment_register (from CALC-A):
>
> supply_cost = unit_cost_usd × total_units
>
> install_rate = 18% (standard Indonesian site)
>
> = 22% (elevated platform \>3 m)
>
> = 25% (decanter centrifuge --- vibration isolation required)
>
> install_cost = supply_cost × install_rate
>
> commissioning = supply_cost × 8%
>
> item_capex = supply_cost + install_cost + commissioning
>
> AGGREGATION:
>
> equip_capex_efb_line = SUM(item_capex) for EFB stream equipment
>
> equip_capex_opdc_line = SUM(item_capex) for OPDC stream equipment
>
> equip_capex_pos_line = SUM(item_capex) for POS stream equipment
>
> equip_capex_shared = SUM(item_capex) for silos, gallery, PLC/HMI
>
> equip_capex_total = SUM of all four lines
>
> ADDITIONAL CAPEX (from CALC-B and CALC-C):
>
> building_civil = portal_frame_kg × rate_usd_per_kg
>
> \+ cladding_area_m2 × rate_usd_per_m2
>
> \+ floor_area_m2 × (150mm RC rate + 200mm truck lane rate)
>
> \+ drainage + foundations
>
> electrical_capex = transformer + switchboard + MCC_panels + cabling
>
> \+ earthing + instrumentation + CCTV + PLC/HMI
>
> platforms_stairs = hot-dip galv. steel platform area_m2 ×
> fabrication_rate
>
> conveyor_gallery = gallery_length_m × 4m × 180 USD/m2
>
> MARGIN ITEMS:
>
> spare_parts_bank = equip_capex_total × 7%
>
> engineering_fee = (equip_capex_total + building_civil + electrical) ×
> 8%
>
> contingency = SUM(all above) × 10%
>
> TOTAL_CAPEX = SUM(all line items)
>
> CAPEX_PER_T_CAPACITY = TOTAL_CAPEX / (stream_tph_efb × 7920 hrs × 0.85
> utilisation)

**Dynamic CAPEX Table Structure (updates every run)**

  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Category**   **Sub-Category**   **Calculation Basis**   **Source Flag**
  -------------- ------------------ ----------------------- ---------------------
  Equipment ---  Trommel, magnets,  CALC-A total_units ×    Quote/Estimate/DATA
  EFB Line       presses ×duty+bkp, unit_cost + 18--22%     GAP per item
                 shredders, mills,  install + 8%            
                 screens, EFB       commissioning           
                 conveyors                                  

  Equipment ---  Trommel, magnet,   CALC-A total_units ×    Quote/Estimate/DATA
  OPDC Line      dewatering press,  unit_cost + install +   GAP per item
                 loosener, buffer   commissioning           
                 bunker, blending                           
                 silo, OPDC                                 
                 conveyors                                  

  Equipment ---  Decanter           CALC-A total_units ×    Quote/Estimate/DATA
  POS Line       centrifuge ×       unit_cost + 25%         GAP
                 duty+bkp, sludge   install + 8%            
                 pump, sump, POS    commissioning           
                 conveyors                                  

  Equipment ---  Buffer silos       CALC-A + CALC-C         Quote/Estimate
  Shared         (EFB+OPDC),                                
                 blending conveyor,                         
                 PLC/HMI per line,                          
                 instrumentation                            

  Building &     Portal frame,      CALC-C structural       Estimate --- obtain
  Civil          cladding (roof + 3 output × current        contractor quote
                 walls), floor      Indonesian unit rates   
                 slabs,                                     
                 foundations,                               
                 drainage, sub-base                         

  Electrical     Transformer, LV    CALC-C electrical       Estimate --- obtain
                 switchboard, MCC   output × standard unit  contractor quote
                 panels, cabling,   rates                   
                 earthing, CCTV                             

  Platforms &    Hot-dip galvanised CALC-C structural +     Estimate
  Staircases     steel platforms at CALC-B platform         
                 +3.0 / +3.2 / +4.0 schedule × fabrication  
                 m elevations +     rate                    
                 staircases                                 

  Conveyor       Steel frame +      CALC-C gallery          Estimate
  Gallery to S2  corrugated iron    dimensions × USD 180/m² 
                 roof, 4 m wide ×                           
                 gallery length m                           

  Spare Parts    Initial wear parts 7% of equipment total   Derived
  Bank           inventory                                  
                 (hammers, screens,                         
                 belts, bearings)                           

  Engineering &  Process, civil,    8% of equipment +       Industry standard
  Design         structural,        building + electrical   
                 electrical                                 
                 drawings and                               
                 specifications                             

  Contingency    Applied to all     10%                     Standard
                 line items above                           

  TOTAL CAPEX    ---                Sum of all above        USD total + USD/t
                                                            capacity
  -------------------------------------------------------------------------------

> **DATA GAP RULE: Every cost item without a confirmed OEM quote or
> contractor estimate must be labelled \'DATA GAP\' in the CAPEX output.
> CFO Professor #35 must review all DATA GAP items before the CAPEX is
> presented to any investor or estate company.**
>
> **CROSS-REFERENCE: All equipment costs must be cross-referenced
> against FD_CFI_Engineering_Master_EPC_UPDATED.xlsx and
> FD_CAPEX_Building_Machinery sheets. Any discrepancy \>15% must be
> flagged explicitly.**

**CALC-E** **MACHINERY OPEX CALCULATOR**

*Annual operating cost for all S1 machinery --- electricity, labour,
wear parts, lubrication --- per year and per tonne fresh substrate*

**Purpose**

Calculates the ongoing cost of operating the S1 facility. Outputs annual
total, cost per tonne fresh substrate, and cost per operating hour. All
inputs are dynamic --- changes in equipment count (CALC-A), building
size (CALC-B), or electricity tariff (AI search Prompt 8) trigger
automatic recalculation.

**OPEX Calculation Logic**

> CONSTANTS:
>
> operating_days_per_year = 330
>
> operating_hours_per_year = 330 × 24 = 7,920 hrs
>
> PLN_rate = \$0.091437/kWh ← UPDATE via AI search every 3 days
>
> ── ELECTRICITY
> ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
>
> For each machine in equipment_register (from CALC-A):
>
> load_factor = 0.85 (press, shredder, mill, trommel, decanter)
>
> = 0.70 (conveyor, feeder, belt scale)
>
> = 0.65 (vibrating screen, sorter)
>
> annual_kWh = motor_kw × duty_units × operating_hrs × load_factor
>
> annual_cost_USD = annual_kWh × PLN_rate
>
> TOTAL electricity_cost = SUM across all equipment + conveyors +
> lighting/HVAC
>
> ── LABOUR
> ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
>
> operators_per_shift = CEIL(total_duty_machines / 4)
>
> shifts_per_day = 3 (24 hr continuous operation)
>
> total_operators = operators_per_shift × 3
>
> maintenance_FTE = 2
>
> supervisor_FTE = 1 per shift = 3
>
> labour_cost = (total_operators × \$8,000) + (maintenance × \$9,500) +
> (supervisors × \$12,000)
>
> \[All USD/year. Update annually via Prompt 8 AI search for Indonesian
> wage indices\]
>
> ── WEAR PARTS
> ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
>
> Hammer mill hammers → replace every 4 weeks → 13 changes/yr
>
> Mill screens → replace every 8 weeks → 6.5 changes/yr
>
> Press feed screws → replace every 6 months → 2 changes/yr
>
> Press pressure screens → replace every 3 months → 4 changes/yr
>
> Conveyor belts → replace every 12 months → 1 per conveyor/yr
>
> Bearings (all machines)→ replace every 6 months per duty machine
>
> Shredder knives/liners → inspect monthly, replace quarterly
>
> ── LUBRICATION
> ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
>
> lube_cost = 1.8% × total_equipment_supply_cost_USD / year
>
> ── TOTALS
> ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
>
> annual_opex = electricity + labour + wear_parts + lube
>
> opex_per_tonne = annual_opex / (stream_tph × 7,920) \[USD/t fresh
> substrate\]
>
> opex_per_hour = annual_opex / 7,920 \[USD/operating hour\]

