**CALC-F** **ASCII PROCESS FLOW GENERATOR**

*Dynamically generates an accurate ASCII process flow diagram from the
live equipment register --- regenerates on every scaling run*

**Purpose**

Produces a machine-accurate ASCII process flow diagram that reflects the
actual equipment count and configuration from CALC-A. If throughput
changes and duty units change, the ASCII diagram shows the updated
configuration with utilisation %, stream parameters, and guardrail gate
status. This is never a static diagram.

**Generation Logic**

> ASCII FLOW GENERATOR --- RULES:
>
> 1\. Read equipment_register from CALC-A, ordered by process_sequence
> field
>
> 2\. For each equipment_item in sequence order:
>
> a\. Draw equipment box (38 chars wide):
>
> Line 1: TAG + EQUIPMENT NAME
>
> Line 2: ×N duty + ×1 backup (if backup_required)
>
> Line 3: Motor: NN kW each \| Util: NN.N% \[COLOUR_FLAG\]
>
> b\. Draw ↓ arrow to next equipment
>
> c\. At SPLIT POINTS (e.g. screen oversize recycle):
>
> Draw ├─ → (oversize back to hammer mill)
>
> Draw └─ → (product forward)
>
> 3\. Show stream state at each connection point:
>
> \[t/h FRESH \| MC: XX% \| size: XXmm\]
>
> 4\. Show GUARDRAIL GATE at critical checkpoints:
>
> ⊕ PASS (green) or ⊗ FAIL --- halt run
>
> Gates: OPDC MC ≤40% \| EFB particle ≤2mm D90 \| pH ≤8.0 before S4
>
> 5\. Show BLEND POINT where EFB + OPDC converge into 60:40 DM blend
>
> 6\. End with BUFFER SILOS → CONVEYOR GALLERY → \[S2 CHEMICAL
> TREATMENT\]
>
> SCALING NOTATION IN BOX:
>
> 1 duty + 1 bkp → shows: \'×1 duty + ×1 backup\'
>
> 3 duty + 1 bkp → shows: \'×3 duty + ×1 backup (AMBER 78%)\'
>
> RED util → shows: \'⚠ OVERLOADED --- add 1 duty unit\'
>
> OUTPUT: ascii_flow_text (stored in Supabase
> s1_run_log.ascii_flow_text)

