**IMMUTABLE GUARDRAILS --- ALL EIGHT CALCULATORS**

The following rules are locked across the entire calculator hub. They
cannot be overridden by user input, AI prompt, or Admin Panel setting.

> **OPDC MOISTURE FLOOR: 40% MC is an absolute floor. The OPDC press
> (PR-301) discharge may never exceed 40% MC. If equipment selection
> cannot achieve this, CALC-A must refuse to proceed and flag for
> engineer review.**
>
> **OPDC YIELD LOCK: OPDC t/h = 15.2% of EFB fresh weight. CALC-A will
> never accept a manually entered OPDC rate. This is a
> biological/process constant, not a user variable.**
>
> **EFB PARTICLE SIZE: 2 mm D90 is the hard gate for S2 loading. The
> CALC-F ASCII flow shows an oversize recycle loop back to HM-201.
> Product that fails the gate (VS-201) cannot proceed to SIL-301.**
>
> **UTILISATION CAP: No duty machine may operate above 85% of its
> derated capacity. CALC-A must add duty units or recommend a larger
> model and display a RED flag before the run completes.**
>
> **BACKUP UNIT: Every machine with motor \>11 kW or classed as
> press/shredder/mill/trommel/decanter/screen must have a minimum 1 hot
> standby backup unit of identical specification.**
>
> **N CONVERSION FACTOR: 4.67 in every CALC-H calculation without
> exception. Using 6.25 is a guardrail violation.**
>
> **OEM DERATE: Asian and Indonesian-fabricated machinery = 65% of
> nameplate. EU and Japanese OEMs = 85% of nameplate. Applied in CALC-A
> before any sizing calculation.**
>
> **DATA GAP: Any item without a confirmed OEM quote or contractor
> estimate must be labelled DATA GAP in CALC-D output. No DATA GAP item
> may be used in investor presentations without CFO Professor #35
> review.**
>
> **5-DAY BIO MINIMUM: Not enforced in S1, but CALC-H must write
> \'five_day_bio_minimum: PENDING --- enforced at S3\' in the s2_payload
> guardrail_gates field so the S3 calculator cannot bypass it.**

